[1] ReachableResults: compute urgencyClass once per group via {@const}
    FILES: frontend/src/lib/components/reachable/ReachableResults.svelte
    urgencyClass(urgency) is invoked at the group header (line 78) and again inside the per-card `{#each groupScreenings}` loop (line 116, `class="leave-badge {urgencyClass(urgency)}"`). Since `urgency` is constant for the whole group, the switch runs once per card unnecessarily. Add a group-scoped const after the existing `{@const groupScreenings = groups[urgency]}` (line 73), e.g. `{@const urgencyCss = urgencyClass(urgency)}`, and reference `{urgencyCss}` at both line 78 and line 116. Output strings byte-identical.

[1] Root layout: extract duplicated app-shell into a {#snippet}
    FILES: frontend/src/routes/+layout.svelte
    The `{#if clerkEnabled}` / `{:else}` branches (lines 37-65) duplicate the shell verbatim: the `<a class="skip-link">`, `<div class="min-h-dvh flex flex-col">` with `<Header cinemas={data?.cinemas ?? []} />`, `<main id="main-content">{@render children()}</main>`, and `<Footer />`. Only the wrapping ClerkProvider plus SyncProvider differ (note both branches already render PostHogProvider/GlobalCmdkBinding/CommandPalette except SyncProvider which is Clerk-only). Define `{#snippet shell()}...{/snippet}` for the shared skip-link + shell block and `{@render shell()}` in both branches, keeping the conditional ClerkProvider/SyncProvider logic. Rendered DOM identical; removes a real drift hazard. Verify the snippet covers exactly the byte-identical portion (skip-link + shell div) and that CommandPalette/GlobalCmdkBinding placement is preserved per-branch.
